CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 31, 1959, pg. 4, reads: "'Y' Drive Begins - The Rev. J. A. Williams, right, of the Baptist Temple Church and a board member of the Homewood - Brushton YMCA, delivered an inspiring message to campaign workers at the kick-off meeting of the 1959 membership enrollment drive at the Centre Avenue YMCA in the latter's gymnasium, Sunday. Fifty per cent of the total organization attended the meeting. Also addressing the workers were Atty. Byrd R. Brown, center, co-chairman of the campaign, and Anthony (Tony) Fountain, left, who represented the Gra-Y Clubs of the 'Y.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rev. J. A. Williams speaking at podium with Byrd Brown and Anthony "Tony" Fountain on left, for kick-off meeting of membership campaign in Centre Avenue YMCA with large toteboard in background
